ead, 16 Hurt in NYC Subway Fire; Blaze Probed as Suspicious: Officials|website=NBC New York|language=en-US|access-date=2020-03-27}}</ref> An \"apparently emotionally disturbed person\" is being questioned in connection to the 110th Street fire.<ref name=\"nbcny-000\"/> Authorities also reported a shopping cart was set on fire aboard the second car of the train.<ref>{{cite web |title=Police Investigating Deadly NYC Subway Fire As A Crime |url=https://talkingpointsmemo.com/news/new-york-subway-fire-crime |accessdate=28 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Aftermath==\nTrain service along the [[IRT Lenox Avenue Line]] were suspended as a result of the incident. [[2 (New York City Subway service)|2]] trains operated along the [[IRT Lexington Avenue Line]] from [[149th Street\u2013Grand Concourse station]] to [[Atlantic Avenue\u2013Barclays Center station]] before resuming regular service while [[3 (New York City Subway service)|3]] trains operated between [[New Lots Avenue station (IRT New Lots Line)|New Lots Avenue]] and [[96th Street station (IRT Broadway\u2013Seventh Avenue Line)|96th Street]] and then via the [[IRT Broadway\u2013Seventh Avenue Line]] to/from [[137th Street\u2013City College station|137th Street\u2013City College]] with service suspended between 96th Street and [[Harlem\u2013148th Street station]]. Shuttle buses operated along the closed stations. 86th Street and 96th Street stations were also temporarily closed in order to allow FDNY to continue their investigation.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://mymtaalerts.com/m?D8D31|title=MANH, 1 Train, FDNY Activity|last=|first=|date=March 27, 2020|website=mymtaalerts.com|publisher=Metropolitan Transportation Authority|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=March 29, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://mymtaalerts.com/m?D8D32|title=UPDATED: BX, 3 Train, FDNY Activity|website=mymtaalerts.com|access-date=2020-03-29}}</ref> Service along the IRT Lenox Avenue Line resumed on March 30 while bypassing [[Central Pa